\begin{document}
$$ L_{{{\text{free}}}} = L_{{{\text{complex}}}} - n_{{{\text{ncp}}}} \cdot 11\,{\text{nm,}} $$\end{document}where nncp is the number of NCPs per complex.

On the basis of the average wrapped DNA length (Lncp ∼120 bp), expected cc-distances (ccexp) for monomer lengths (Lmono) of 172 and 208 bp (58 and 71 nm, respectively) can be calculated assuming that 2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
